This article is a transcript of a press gaggle by Jay Carney and Ben Rhodes aboard Air Force One en route to Johannesburg, South Africa. They discuss the details of President Obama's trip to South Africa for Nelson Mandela's memorial service. They mention the notable people onboard the flight, including former President Bush and former First Lady Laura Bush, former Secretary of State Hillary Clinton, National Security Advisor Susan Rice, and Attorney General Eric Holder. They also discuss the possibility of President Obama meeting with the Mandela family or Iranian President Rouhani. They talk about the U.S. delegation for the memorial service and the logistics of the event. They mention the security concerns and the President's upcoming speech, which will reflect on Nelson Mandela's impact and legacy. They also address the recent comments made by Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu regarding new sanctions on Iran and the ongoing budget negotiations in Congress.